# [EDIT]
# Change global parameters in this section instead further below
#   CB_LOCATION:  set to World except for the master installation in Aachen;
#                 specify a custom value here to distinguish your installation
#   JAVA_CAPABLE: the platform(s) for which the Java compiler is invoked
#                 format: /platform1/platform2/.../platformn/
#   TEX_CAPABLE:  the platform(s) for which the LaTeX processor is invoked
#                 format: like JAVA_CAPABLE
#   JAVADIR:      directory that contains the executables java and javac
#   CC:           path to executable C compiler (e.g. gcc-4.4 or earlier)
#   CXX:          path to executable C++ compiler (e.g. g++-4.4 or earlier)
#   SWI_HOME:     installation directory of SWI-Prolog; note that you need to 
#                 compile SWI-Prolog from the sources (www.swi-prolog.org) 
#                 because the packages from some Linux repositories are not
#                 complete for system development
#  SWI_INCLUDE:   directory that contains SWI-Prolog.h
#
# Parameters enclosed with ifndef can be globally defined by environment variables
# (e.g. from .bashrc)

